WHAT GOT BUILT

**1. Keyword Map — 3 tiers**
Tier 1 is local transactional: "electrician pittsburg ks", city-specific variants, and the service-area long tails. These are the calls-and-money terms. Tier 2 is service-specific transactional — one term per route so every service page owns a real query. Tier 3 is informational blog targets aimed at featured snippets and AI overviews, which build topical authority and funnel visitors who are researching before they call.

**2. On-page rules site-wide**
Canonical tags, mobile-first requirements, Core Web Vitals targets, and the internal link mandate — every service page must link to Pittsburg and to estimate-prep, every city page must link back to services. These run before Forge touches a single component.

**3. Route-by-route: slug / H1 / title tag / meta description**
Every one of the 19 routes in the brief has exact copy. Title tags are under 60 chars, metas under 160. Nothing generic — each is tuned to its target keyword and includes the phone number or a conversion signal where it fits.

**4. Schema notes**
LocalBusiness + Electrician dual @type on homepage and city pages. Service schema on all 6 service routes. BreadcrumbList everywhere. FAQPage on 3 high-value routes. Review schema on /reviews. The JSON-LD blocks are ready to drop in. Joplin note is in there — JAG is KS-licensed so the Joplin page copy is framed as "near Joplin" not "serving Joplin MO."

**5. Internal link plan**
Hub-and-spoke with homepage as center. Every spoke links back, links to estimate-prep, and links laterally to one or two related services. Footer NAP + full service/city link block specified.

**6. GBP post drafts — 8 posts, 2 months**
Each is ready to queue in GHL for Toby approval before push. Service spotlights, review pull-quote post, who-we-are trust post, service area callout, commercial callout, fixtures, and a Q&A seed post. Five owner-posted Q&A entries included.

**7. 30-day content + ad calendar**
Week-by-week, day-by-day. GSC sitemap submission day 1. GBP post cadence every 5-7 days. Three blog posts timed with internal link additions. Ad draft gated on day 28 — draft only, no spend, LSA structure for Toby to approve with license upload requirement called out explicitly.

**8. NAP consistency anchor**
Exact canonical format for every citation, on-page mention, and GBP field. No variations.

Nothing else in the repo was touched. Forge and Craig can consume this directly.
